I mixed this with WF Pixie Stick Candy 0.75% and no Jackfruit or Rainbow CandyI totally understand now why you said that you fixed medicinal cherry! &#xD;
&#xD;
Is it the best recipe?, of course not, but that is not the point, although it is good and I can vape the 15ml I made. But man, that cherry is totally fixed. While I was mixing it I tasted the apricot and could noticed some shared notes and I think it smooth the sharp edges of the cherry. I don't notice the "candy" flavor at all, and the cherry is sweet and natural. I thought that the sweet guava would be off but I imagine it is to lift the general flavor because I do notice that the grape compound in the candy mutes the flavor a little bit. Congratulations Alfred, not only the final product, but the process behind it is incredible!
